modules.description: This module implements message sending and receiving over sockets with support for ancillary data, specifically enabling file descriptor passing between processes. It provides `send` and `recv` functions for single buffer I/O, and `sendv` and `recvv` for scatter-gather I/O, all operating on `Unix.file_descr` sockets. Concrete use cases include inter-process communication where file descriptors need to be transmitted, such as passing open files or sockets between processes securely.
